  "prompt": "Who is best hockey player of 2015?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" hockey player can be subjective and varies depending on criteria such as individual performance, impact on the team, and personal accolades. However, in 2015, many would argue that Alexander Ovechkin of the Washington Capitals and Sidney Crosby of the Pittsburgh Penguins were among the top contenders for the title of best hockey player.\n\nAlexander Ovechkin won the Maurice \"Rocket\" Richard Trophy for leading the NHL in goals, scoring 53 goals during the 2014-2015 season. \n\nSidney Crosby continued to be a dominant force in the league, contributing significantly to his team and maintaining high levels of performance.\n\nBoth players are highly celebrated for their skills and achievements in the sport.",
